						<div class="postbody">I avoid using pointers in cc65 as well, as I know they tend to behave worse than arrays. Sometimes you have to, as pointed. But it's fun how you better use array access when possible when targetting the 6502 via cc65, but you better use pointer based access when possible when targetting the Z80 via z88dk or SDCC. Sometimes porting is a nightmare because of this <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":-D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

					
