						<div class="postbody">Yeah, looks like every pointer access of any kind does that.<br /><br />Unfortunately, I still need pointers if a character has a certain movement pattern that is stored in an array.<br /><br />I wrote some macros for this kind of stuff now, like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">#define AsmSetVariableFromZpArrayPointer(variable, zpArrayPointer, index)\<br />{\<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;__asm__(&quot;LDY %v&quot;, index);\<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;__asm__(&quot;LDA (%v), Y&quot;, zpArrayPointer);\<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;__asm__(&quot;STA %v&quot;, variable);\<br />}</div></div>

					
