				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's actually correct. The temporary result <strong>src + 3</strong> is implicitly a 16-bit int. The high bits of the result can matter when you shift them down, but they won't matter when you shift them up. Think of <strong>(255+3)&gt;&gt;2</strong>.<br /><br />How does it deal with:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">dest = (unsigned char)(src + 3) &gt;&gt; 2;</div></div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> on Wed Jun 27, 2018 4:00 pm, edited 1 time in total.</span>
